      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>''One danger of Iran going nuclear has always been that it might provoke others. So when you see the development of nuclear power elsewhere in the region, it's a cause for some concern.''</p>
        <p>MARK FITZPATRICK, of the International Institute for Strategic Studies, on a trend of Middle East states seeking nuclear capabilities. [1]</p>
